Corys: Thank you, Sorceress Luna, for helping Mao and Mei.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Corys-san, you're part of the resistance as well, aren't you?

Corys: Yes. But we're in a state of ruin. We tried to launch a surprise attack
on Lucia and the generals of Valentina, but as you can see, our soldiers have
been gravely injured...
Corys: That's why I had Mao and Mei go to fetch the "Gra Herb."
\C[24][Becky]\C[0] I see. So we're not the only ones who wanted the Gra Herb.

\C[24][Cain]\C[0] Attacking Lucia and her group with that number of people is reckless. We
couldn't lay a finger on them either.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Corys-san, please use the Gra Herb for yourselves.
Corys: Is that really okay?
\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Wait a minute, Luna! After all the trouble we went through to find it!

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] We can find more medicine. Besides, the people here are more seriously injured.
I'm sure Noah would understand too.
\C[24][Becky]\C[0] You're just too kind-hearted...
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Please don't worry about us and use the Gra Herb.
Corys: I am deeply grateful...
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] By the way, Corys-san, may I ask if you know someone named "Regnus Grahardt"?
Corys: Regnus Grahardt? No, I've never heard of him.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Is that so...
Corys: Who is that person?

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] He's someone we, as the resistance, are looking for. If Regnus Grahardt were
here, he might be able to stand against Lucia and the generals of Valentina.

Corys: Such a person couldn't possibly exist. Lucia is a direct descendant of
sorcerers. And the generals of Valentina have godlike strength. Even if he did
exist, there's no way he could defeat Lucia and her group. Are such dream-like
stories even possible?

\C[24][Cain]\C[0] Hey, hey, knowing you couldn't win, you still challenged Lucia and her group?
That's foolish.

Corys: Yes, it's foolish. But we can no longer endure Lucia's tyranny. We are
made to work like slaves every day.
Corys: Our hope, the Knights of Messiah, won't move a muscle. It's all over.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Have you met with Lord Ceres?
Corys: Yes. I've been to Moorduna several times, but the answer was always no.

Corys: Ceres Arianne won't budge. The Knights of Messiah seem intent on leaving
us to die. Moorduna is afraid of Jupiterino and Valentina. It might be
inevitable.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] I believe Lord Ceres must have some plan in mind. Perhaps she intends to
negotiate with Valentina.

Corys: I can't imagine the magical kingdom of Valentina would listen to anything
Moorduna has to say.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Is that so...
